# An [[ancient]] [[divination]] method of the [[Highland]] [[Scots]]: the [[oracle]] of the [[hide]], in which a person was sewn into the hide of a freshly-killed [[ox]] and placed beside a [[waterfall]]. This would enable him to foresee the results of an impending [[battle]].
#: {{rfquotek|Sir Walter Scott, ''The Lady of the Lake''}}
# An ancient divination method of the Highland Scots, in which [[cat]]s were roasted alive to call up the [[spirit]] of the [[demon]] cat who would grant the wishes of the torturers.
